MAB-Record

Module for handling B<MAB2> (Maschinelles Austauschformat für Bibliotheken)
records as objects. At the moment the package only supports reading of MAB2
records. The decoding of records is handled by MAB::File::MAB2. For 
handling of file with multiple records use MAB::File or MAB::Batch.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc MAB::Record

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=MAB-Record

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/MAB-Record

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/MAB-Record

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/MAB-Record/


